            <abstract>The control problem of the spectrum of a linear matrix second-order  system with one-input
                and multi-output feedback in the form of a first-order dynamic compensator is solved.
                Necessary and sufficient conditions for the existence of a solution to the problem are considered
                and an algorithm for calculating the feedback parameters is described.
                A numerical example is given. A feature of the proposed approach is that the compensator
                contains only one first-order equation, in contrast to classical observers and full- and
                reduced-order dynamic compensators.</abstract>
            <title>Control of Spectrum of Second-order Matrix System with Dynamic Output Feedback</title>
            <keywords>
                <word>control of spectrum</word>
